WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:00.770 --> 00:00:02.520
Hey!

3
00:00:02.520 --> 00:00:05.490
You guys! Anyone there?!

4
00:00:05.490 --> 00:00:07.650
Where is it?

5
00:00:09.780 --> 00:00:13.080
Where did it go?!

6
00:00:13.080 --> 00:00:15.080
G-Gedatsu, sir...

7
00:00:15.080 --> 00:00:17.830
Y-Your eyes are rolled
baack in your head.

8
00:00:17.830 --> 00:00:21.130
In that state, you cannot see a thing.

9
00:00:21.130 --> 00:00:22.210
How careless of me!

10
00:00:23.480 --> 00:00:25.460
Please look at this photo.

11
00:00:26.460 --> 00:00:27.720
That one...

12
00:00:27.720 --> 00:00:29.260
That puny creature.

13
00:00:30.180 --> 00:00:32.300
He's with the Blue Sea people!

14
00:00:32.300 --> 00:00:33.640
For real...?

15
00:00:34.180 --> 00:00:36.060
It's not a tanuki?

16
00:00:36.430 --> 00:00:37.560
Tanuki?

17
00:00:37.560 --> 00:00:39.850
Sir, that is no wild animal.

18
00:00:40.650 --> 00:00:43.900
It is unquestionably
a creature from the Blue Sea!

19
00:00:44.400 --> 00:00:45.940
Luffy!

20
00:00:45.940 --> 00:00:48.280
Where'd you go?!

21
00:00:48.280 --> 00:00:50.030
Zoro!

22
00:00:50.030 --> 00:00:51.780
Robin!

23
00:00:51.780 --> 00:00:54.450
Hurry and come here!

24
00:00:54.450 --> 00:00:57.910
Where are you guys...?!

25
00:00:57.910 --> 00:01:00.540
I'm starting to get worried!

26
00:01:00.540 --> 00:01:01.620
Hey!

27
00:01:01.620 --> 00:01:03.210
Guys!

28
00:01:03.210 --> 00:01:06.050
It's me!

29
00:01:12.930 --> 00:01:14.510
Where is it?!

30
00:01:27.860 --> 00:01:30.150
Where did it go?!

31
00:01:35.280 --> 00:01:36.830
Yikes!

32
00:01:36.830 --> 00:01:39.950
Wh-What is this...?!

33
00:01:57.970 --> 00:02:01.180
Did you know there's an awesome treasure at the end of this sea?!

34
00:02:01.180 --> 00:02:03.980
And whoever gets it becomes King of the Pirates!

35
00:02:03.980 --> 00:02:05.600
Isn't that exciting?!

36
00:02:05.600 --> 00:02:08.650
Cool new adventures are waiting out there!

37
00:02:11.040 --> 00:02:18.700
BON VOYAGE! Light the ember of courage and let the fire grow

38
00:02:18.700 --> 00:02:26.300
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

39
00:02:26.420 --> 00:02:28.850
Back when we first started

40
00:02:28.850 --> 00:02:34.070
we had separate ideas about where we would soon go

41
00:02:34.380 --> 00:02:36.020
Things have changed now,

42
00:02:36.020 --> 00:02:41.080
when we look towards our dreams we all share one telescope

43
00:02:41.370 --> 00:02:46.320
When you find that your heart's been led astray

44
00:02:46.320 --> 00:02:50.620
time to calibrate your compasses

45
00:02:50.620 --> 00:02:53.650
Set a new course, turn the tables now

46
00:02:53.650 --> 00:03:00.940
BON VOYAGE! Shed your previous baggage, forget the past

47
00:03:00.940 --> 00:03:07.780
Smiles can weather a storm, we know that better than anyone

48
00:03:07.780 --> 00:03:09.720
Don't you fret,

49
00:03:09.720 --> 00:03:15.540
tears shed along the way to your dreams are not in vain

50
00:03:15.540 --> 00:03:21.740
You know that you're all PRECIOUS IN MY LIFE

51
00:03:22.700 --> 00:03:29.850
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

52
00:03:30.730 --> 00:03:35.570
<b>Pirate Chopper vs. Priest Gedatsu</b>

53
00:03:40.120 --> 00:03:42.160
What's wrong, Straw Hat?!

54
00:03:43.240 --> 00:03:46.290
I know you haven't met
your demise just yet!

55
00:03:46.290 --> 00:03:48.120
Yeah!

56
00:03:48.120 --> 00:03:49.880
Of course not!

57
00:04:04.470 --> 00:04:07.310
Ahh! Wh-Wh-What...?! Wh-What the...?!

58
00:04:13.730 --> 00:04:14.940
What happened?!

59
00:04:20.410 --> 00:04:23.450
Where did he go?

60
00:04:25.910 --> 00:04:27.080
No matter.

61
00:04:27.960 --> 00:04:31.920
This is no time to be wasting
energy on someone like him.

62
00:04:31.920 --> 00:04:33.380
What I need to do...

63
00:04:35.210 --> 00:04:39.550
is save my strength
for when I face Enel!

64
00:04:40.010 --> 00:04:45.640
If I use another reject, my body
will probably be blown to bits.

65
00:04:47.060 --> 00:04:50.520
I'm coming for you, Enel!

66
00:04:57.940 --> 00:04:59.900
It finally stopped...

67
00:05:00.700 --> 00:05:03.070
Where... am I?!

68
00:05:10.580 --> 00:05:12.580
Why, he...!

69
00:05:12.580 --> 00:05:15.170
He... He killed...

70
00:05:16.630 --> 00:05:18.340
He killed Sanji!

71
00:05:18.340 --> 00:05:19.720
It's no use!

72
00:05:20.090 --> 00:05:23.090
His heart isn't beating at all!

73
00:05:23.090 --> 00:05:24.300
Hey! Sanji!

74
00:05:24.300 --> 00:05:26.970
Sanji! Sanji!

75
00:05:27.390 --> 00:05:28.270
Damn...

76
00:05:28.270 --> 00:05:30.810
If only Chopper were here...

77
00:05:30.810 --> 00:05:32.140
Wait, Usopp!

78
00:05:32.520 --> 00:05:34.480
That's his right side!

79
00:05:34.480 --> 00:05:36.650
The heart's on the left!

80
00:05:36.150 --> 00:05:36.400
<b>His
Right
Side</b>

81
00:05:36.650 --> 00:05:36.900
<b>His
Right
Side</b>

82
00:05:37.150 --> 00:05:37.400
<b>His
Right
Side</b>

83
00:05:37.650 --> 00:05:38.440
<b>His
Right
Side</b>

84
00:05:40.820 --> 00:05:42.070
It's beating!

85
00:05:43.610 --> 00:05:45.240
Thank goodness!

86
00:05:45.240 --> 00:05:46.580
He came back to life!

87
00:05:47.080 --> 00:05:49.830
But he can still die
from these injuries!

88
00:05:49.830 --> 00:05:50.960
He can?!

89
00:05:50.960 --> 00:05:52.460
Oh crap!

90
00:05:52.460 --> 00:05:53.670
This is bad!

91
00:05:57.000 --> 00:06:02.050
H-Hey! What the hell
did you do to Sanji?!

92
00:06:11.980 --> 00:06:13.350
Curse you...!

93
00:06:17.060 --> 00:06:19.280
Stay yourselves...

94
00:06:19.730 --> 00:06:21.440
and I will do nothing.

95
00:06:22.450 --> 00:06:24.030
Are we clear?

96
00:06:26.320 --> 00:06:27.620
Good.

97
00:06:27.620 --> 00:06:29.200
Who is this guy?!

98
00:06:29.910 --> 00:06:31.910
What did he do just now...?!

99
00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:37.170
What in blazes are you thinking?!

100
00:06:37.170 --> 00:06:42.340
The subjects I seized from you when I
invaded this island six years ago...

101
00:06:42.800 --> 00:06:47.890
are serving me with
the utmost diligence.

102
00:06:50.060 --> 00:06:53.600
My Holy Host...

103
00:06:53.980 --> 00:06:56.100
They're a strapping bunch...

104
00:06:56.600 --> 00:06:58.560
and are indeed talented.

105
00:06:59.440 --> 00:07:06.070
Nonetheless, it seems their six years
of diligent service is nearing its end.

106
00:07:06.700 --> 00:07:11.950
What's more, this island has
outlived its usefulness,

107
00:07:11.950 --> 00:07:15.830
so I thought it fitting
to bid you farewell.

108
00:07:15.830 --> 00:07:18.080
That is all.

109
00:07:21.340 --> 00:07:27.260
However, the denizens
of Skypiea are all ignorant fools.

110
00:07:27.260 --> 00:07:32.680
They view this island as a mere
clump of vearth after all.

111
00:07:32.680 --> 00:07:34.480
What are you getting at?

112
00:07:34.850 --> 00:07:39.940
The reason we seized this island...

113
00:07:40.730 --> 00:07:44.990
the reason the Blue Sea flies
stepped foot onto this island...

114
00:07:45.440 --> 00:07:51.910
and the reason the Shandians are intent on
returning to their home are not at all different.

115
00:07:51.910 --> 00:07:53.540
In other words...

116
00:07:53.540 --> 00:07:57.790
there is but one thing
everyone seeks on this island!

117
00:08:00.710 --> 00:08:07.090
That being everyone's desires for
the glorious relics of Shandora,

118
00:08:07.680 --> 00:08:11.140
the legendary City of Gold that
prospered in the Blue Sea long ago!

119
00:08:13.310 --> 00:08:15.140
Gold...?

120
00:08:15.140 --> 00:08:17.350
And that is...?

121
00:08:19.730 --> 00:08:22.360
Like I said... Ignorant!

122
00:08:22.360 --> 00:08:27.820
There isn't a soul up here that knows
about gold, much less its value!

123
00:08:28.860 --> 00:08:32.240
Funnily enough, this game
is the final battle.

124
00:08:32.240 --> 00:08:38.500
The winner of this survival game will
make this bounty of gold their own.

125
00:08:41.790 --> 00:08:43.500
Can you hear it?

126
00:08:43.500 --> 00:08:46.260
The sounds of the lively festival...

127
00:08:51.180 --> 00:08:53.260
As a matter of fact,

128
00:08:53.260 --> 00:08:57.220
I'm a participant myself,
so I must be off.

129
00:08:57.640 --> 00:08:59.140
Wait, Enel!

130
00:08:59.140 --> 00:09:00.270
The Holy Host...

131
00:09:00.270 --> 00:09:02.350
Will you release them
from servitude?!

132
00:09:03.860 --> 00:09:07.320
As they say, "God only knows."

133
00:09:08.440 --> 00:09:10.320
Wait, Enel!

134
00:09:10.780 --> 00:09:12.110
He's gone...

135
00:09:15.990 --> 00:09:16.950
Usopp!

136
00:09:25.840 --> 00:09:27.710
Out of the way!

137
00:09:35.010 --> 00:09:36.510
Not another one!

138
00:09:41.850 --> 00:09:44.940
I can't be bothered with these
riffraff warrior monks!

139
00:09:49.900 --> 00:09:52.910
That's some rare ammunition
you have there.

140
00:09:52.910 --> 00:09:57.660
A heavy element that normally
can't be found in the sky...

141
00:09:58.200 --> 00:10:01.160
The vearth mineral, iron?

142
00:10:06.130 --> 00:10:12.880
It seems you've taken down
many of my men, Shandian.

143
00:10:12.880 --> 00:10:17.140
You must be Genbo, one of their
front-line attackers, yes?

144
00:10:18.260 --> 00:10:20.930
And you're their abbot, Yama!

145
00:10:21.680 --> 00:10:24.230
Now, outta my way!

146
00:10:47.790 --> 00:10:49.710
Damn you...

147
00:10:51.510 --> 00:10:53.800
I-I refuse...

148
00:10:54.930 --> 00:10:57.800
to die in a place like this!

149
00:10:58.220 --> 00:10:59.680
Oh!

150
00:10:59.680 --> 00:11:01.930
You're still alive.

151
00:11:01.930 --> 00:11:03.980
You're certainly tough.

152
00:11:03.980 --> 00:11:05.190
Very well.

153
00:11:05.190 --> 00:11:08.770
To honor your
spirit of determination...

154
00:11:09.150 --> 00:11:13.740
I will finish you off
with my secret technique.

155
00:11:19.120 --> 00:11:21.200
Tenfold Axe!

156
00:11:21.660 --> 00:11:25.330
Damn you, Yama!

157
00:11:31.840 --> 00:11:34.170
Axe Mountain!

158
00:11:45.060 --> 00:11:47.440
You were so close.

159
00:11:47.440 --> 00:11:50.270
You did well to make it this far.

160
00:11:58.910 --> 00:11:59.990
What?!

161
00:11:59.990 --> 00:12:01.490
Who are you?!

162
00:12:02.830 --> 00:12:04.450
Don't give us, "What?!"

163
00:12:04.450 --> 00:12:06.580
– We're the priors!
– We're the priors!

164
00:12:06.580 --> 00:12:08.460
You killed our brother Satori!

165
00:12:08.460 --> 00:12:10.460
You killed him!

166
00:12:10.460 --> 00:12:14.670
What?! I don't know
any brother of yours!

167
00:12:17.680 --> 00:12:21.180
Don't play dumb! My name is Hotori!

168
00:12:21.930 --> 00:12:24.560
My name is Kotori!

169
00:12:24.560 --> 00:12:27.940
– You guys killed our brother!
– You guys killed our brother!

170
00:12:29.600 --> 00:12:32.110
I told you, I don't know
what you're talking about!

171
00:12:32.110 --> 00:12:34.820
– We'll make you pay!
– We'll make you pay!

172
00:12:35.190 --> 00:12:36.820
Pierre!

173
00:12:42.320 --> 00:12:45.330
I will dispatch them
and catch up to Enel posthaste.

174
00:12:45.330 --> 00:12:49.460
There is no telling what he
might do to my subordinates!

175
00:13:00.720 --> 00:13:02.340
Stand back, girl!

176
00:13:02.340 --> 00:13:06.140
Though I am wounded,
I will not fall to them!

177
00:13:06.140 --> 00:13:07.270
No!

178
00:13:07.270 --> 00:13:08.600
Sometimes...

179
00:13:10.140 --> 00:13:11.310
even I...

180
00:13:11.770 --> 00:13:13.690
have to protect these guys!

181
00:13:17.070 --> 00:13:18.690
Very well!

182
00:13:19.190 --> 00:13:21.820
First, ascertain their dials!

183
00:13:21.820 --> 00:13:22.870
Got it!

184
00:13:23.660 --> 00:13:26.450
– We're going to avenge our brother!
– We're going to avenge our brother!

185
00:13:53.600 --> 00:13:56.730
A memorial for the very city itself...

186
00:14:00.720 --> 00:14:02.910
that was built by descendants...

187
00:14:03.450 --> 00:14:05.410
after the city fell.

188
00:14:07.740 --> 00:14:08.950
Shandora...

189
00:14:09.750 --> 00:14:11.870
That was this ancient city's name...

190
00:14:17.040 --> 00:14:19.250
Year 402 of the pelagic calendar.

191
00:14:19.630 --> 00:14:24.390
The city flourished
over 1,100 years ago,

192
00:14:24.390 --> 00:14:26.600
and it was 800 years ago when it fell.

193
00:14:29.850 --> 00:14:35.060
That was during the Void Century,
the gap in the world's history.

194
00:14:35.850 --> 00:14:40.940
This island may possess
the unspoken history...

195
00:14:41.690 --> 00:14:43.780
that's gone from the world below.

196
00:14:46.030 --> 00:14:48.030
This is a complete map of Shandora...

197
00:14:48.870 --> 00:14:54.830
Perhaps the city's center holds more
clues about this unspeakable history...

198
00:14:55.290 --> 00:14:56.000
Who...?!

199
00:14:56.580 --> 00:14:58.880
Why, hello there, cutie-pie.

200
00:15:07.680 --> 00:15:09.350
Where did you disappear to?!

201
00:15:13.100 --> 00:15:14.640
A concealment technique?!

202
00:15:14.640 --> 00:15:15.520
Ah!

203
00:15:15.520 --> 00:15:17.600
His eyes are rolled back in his head!

204
00:15:17.600 --> 00:15:19.820
It looks real scary!

205
00:15:25.320 --> 00:15:28.700
Gedatsu, sir! You cannot see
the enemy with your eyes like that!

206
00:15:30.080 --> 00:15:31.200
How careless of me!

207
00:15:32.330 --> 00:15:33.870
Is he that stupid?!

208
00:15:35.250 --> 00:15:37.370
Enemy?! I guess I am, huh?!

209
00:15:37.370 --> 00:15:39.880
You wouldn't happen
to be a priest, would you?!

210
00:15:46.090 --> 00:15:47.760
Indeed, I am!

211
00:15:47.760 --> 00:15:48.760
Heso!

212
00:15:48.760 --> 00:15:49.430
Huh?

213
00:15:49.430 --> 00:15:55.180
My name is Sky Punk Gedatsu,
priest of the almighty God Enel!

214
00:15:55.180 --> 00:15:59.020
I am in charge of Upper Yard's
Ordeal of Swamp!

215
00:15:59.980 --> 00:16:02.440
Say something already, you jerk!

216
00:16:04.110 --> 00:16:07.150
Gedatsu, sir! He cannot hear you
unless you speak out loud!

217
00:16:07.820 --> 00:16:09.070
How careless of me!

218
00:16:09.070 --> 00:16:11.280
Who forgets something like that?!

219
00:16:15.450 --> 00:16:18.170
You had best watch your step!

220
00:16:18.170 --> 00:16:21.630
I am already in control of this area!

221
00:16:22.130 --> 00:16:24.130
We are surrounded by swamp clouds!

222
00:16:24.130 --> 00:16:29.220
Once you're caught by one, there is
no way to escape on your own!

223
00:16:29.220 --> 00:16:32.800
The survival rate here is 50 percent...!

224
00:16:32.800 --> 00:16:34.140
How careless of me!

225
00:16:34.140 --> 00:16:35.180
Swamp?!

226
00:16:35.180 --> 00:16:36.980
The Ordeal of Swamp!

227
00:16:37.680 --> 00:16:39.900
You're sinking?!

228
00:16:39.900 --> 00:16:42.360
Fool! It has no effect on me!

229
00:16:42.860 --> 00:16:44.270
Swamp Cloud...

230
00:16:45.480 --> 00:16:48.700
Milky Dials!

231
00:16:54.660 --> 00:16:57.580
Wow! Awesome!

232
00:16:58.910 --> 00:17:02.080
He's shooting stuff
out of his feet to fly!

233
00:17:04.670 --> 00:17:06.260
That's so cool!

234
00:17:09.840 --> 00:17:11.840
Something came out
of his hands, too...

235
00:17:11.840 --> 00:17:15.810
A single tanuki will be
no trouble at all.

236
00:17:16.970 --> 00:17:17.930
Take this!

237
00:17:18.930 --> 00:17:21.440
Swamp Cloud Burger!

238
00:17:22.190 --> 00:17:26.610
The weight of a cloud, but the properties
of a swamp: touching it spells your doom!

239
00:17:28.280 --> 00:17:30.400
Gedatsu, sir! No!
I'm not the one you're–

240
00:17:38.790 --> 00:17:40.620
He can't get it off!

241
00:17:42.330 --> 00:17:44.710
Right, it's a cloud after all!

242
00:17:44.710 --> 00:17:47.300
You can't lift it if your
hands pass through!

243
00:17:51.430 --> 00:17:55.260
The more you struggle to get it off,
the deeper you're dragged inside...

244
00:18:00.100 --> 00:18:01.140
I have to help him!

245
00:18:01.140 --> 00:18:03.440
Found you, tanuki!

246
00:18:03.810 --> 00:18:06.150
Swamp Cloud Burger!

247
00:18:10.110 --> 00:18:12.360
Yikes! If one of those
hits me, I'm dead!

248
00:18:15.200 --> 00:18:17.200
Hey, you!

249
00:18:17.200 --> 00:18:19.160
Are you all right?! Hang in there!

250
00:18:19.830 --> 00:18:20.540
Hey!

251
00:18:21.870 --> 00:18:23.540
Breathe!

252
00:18:24.000 --> 00:18:25.500
Don't die!

253
00:18:29.800 --> 00:18:31.130
Good! You're alive!

254
00:18:33.130 --> 00:18:35.640
I owe you my life...

255
00:18:38.680 --> 00:18:41.020
Being saved by an enemy...

256
00:18:41.020 --> 00:18:42.520
Pathetic!

257
00:18:42.520 --> 00:18:43.310
Uh-oh!

258
00:18:44.140 --> 00:18:46.400
How daare you speak that way!

259
00:18:46.400 --> 00:18:49.110
Unforgivable! My service
to you ends here!

260
00:18:50.440 --> 00:18:53.370
You'll answer to my axe dial!

261
00:18:54.610 --> 00:18:57.700
Alright! We can do it!
Let's fight together!

262
00:18:57.700 --> 00:18:59.160
Very well.

263
00:18:59.160 --> 00:19:00.870
Jet Punch!

264
00:19:14.510 --> 00:19:17.090
The destructive jet dial!

265
00:19:17.090 --> 00:19:19.140
If you accelerate your punch with it,

266
00:19:19.140 --> 00:19:22.430
your opponent doesn't even
have time to feel his own defeat.

267
00:19:23.560 --> 00:19:26.600
Though the fact that it rips
clothing is a problem...

268
00:19:26.940 --> 00:19:29.730
This is a priest?!

269
00:19:30.230 --> 00:19:33.440
If I don't run away with
all I've got... I'm dead!

270
00:19:38.370 --> 00:19:39.870
No, stay off the clouds!

271
00:19:39.870 --> 00:19:41.660
There are swamp cloud traps!

272
00:19:42.540 --> 00:19:45.000
I'll go above the ruins to the forest!

273
00:19:50.210 --> 00:19:53.670
Where do you think
you're going, tanuki?

274
00:19:55.260 --> 00:19:57.130
Jet Punch!

275
00:19:57.130 --> 00:19:58.430
Rumble!

276
00:19:58.430 --> 00:19:59.720
Jumping Point!

277
00:20:03.520 --> 00:20:05.810
Rumble balls last for three minutes...

278
00:20:05.810 --> 00:20:08.310
So! You have zoan powers!

279
00:20:11.400 --> 00:20:12.360
It's no use!

280
00:20:12.360 --> 00:20:14.320
Jet Punch!

281
00:20:14.690 --> 00:20:15.820
Heavy Point!

282
00:20:18.860 --> 00:20:20.950
Swamp Cloud Burger!

283
00:20:20.950 --> 00:20:22.280
That again...!

284
00:20:22.830 --> 00:20:24.330
Guard Point!

285
00:20:27.370 --> 00:20:29.880
How dare you be so insolent!

286
00:20:29.880 --> 00:20:31.460
Brain Point!

287
00:20:33.340 --> 00:20:34.300
Scope!

288
00:20:34.920 --> 00:20:37.260
A weak point...!
Some sort of weak point...!

289
00:20:37.590 --> 00:20:40.640
Anything will do! I gotta find
an opening and escape!

290
00:20:40.640 --> 00:20:43.430
Jet Punch!

291
00:20:52.690 --> 00:20:53.820
I even...

292
00:20:54.440 --> 00:20:55.780
had my guard up...

293
00:21:02.570 --> 00:21:03.280
Look!

294
00:21:04.160 --> 00:21:07.370
There it is, wreathed
in clouds...! Giant Jack!

295
00:21:09.370 --> 00:21:11.750
We're nearing the ruins of Shandora!

296
00:21:13.750 --> 00:21:15.500
Enel is at the top!

297
00:21:26.930 --> 00:21:28.640
You called?

298
00:21:31.100 --> 00:21:33.810
I'm right here.

299
00:21:37.110 --> 00:21:38.440
Did you want something?

300
00:21:41.610 --> 00:21:44.830
Warrior of Shandora, Kamakiri...

301
00:21:45.410 --> 00:21:47.910
Enel! To hell with you!

302
00:21:48.660 --> 00:21:51.620
Who do you think you're talking to?

303
00:21:52.120 --> 00:21:54.210
I am God, you know.

304
00:21:55.590 --> 00:22:01.760
You seem absolutely baffled
as to why I've appeared here.

305
00:22:03.090 --> 00:22:04.220
Your mantra...?!

306
00:22:07.510 --> 00:22:12.060
I don't need that to see
what's written all over your face!

307
00:22:13.650 --> 00:22:15.400
Though, I don't blame you.

308
00:22:15.400 --> 00:22:20.280
Normally, I wouldn't need to
bother getting my hands dirty.

309
00:22:20.280 --> 00:22:23.360
But you see, I'm also a player
in this survival game...

310
00:22:23.360 --> 00:22:25.990
and I shall soon depart this land.

311
00:22:25.990 --> 00:22:29.830
In fact, I just finished
saying goodbye to Gan Fall.

312
00:22:32.000 --> 00:22:34.750
Is this a game to you?!
Stop playing around!

313
00:22:35.210 --> 00:22:39.420
You look like you really
want to get rid of me...

314
00:22:40.840 --> 00:22:41.970
Splendid!

315
00:22:43.010 --> 00:22:49.470
I will reward you for all your
tribulations as a warrior...

316
00:22:49.470 --> 00:22:51.730
Call it the magnanimity of God.

317
00:22:53.230 --> 00:22:54.440
Let's see...

318
00:22:54.440 --> 00:22:56.310
How does five minutes sound?

319
00:22:56.310 --> 00:22:59.820
I will sit right here
for five minutes' time.

320
00:22:59.820 --> 00:23:00.900
What?!

321
00:23:01.360 --> 00:23:05.450
I will neither dodge
your attacks nor strike back.

322
00:23:05.450 --> 00:23:08.240
Come at me with no reservations.

323
00:23:10.660 --> 00:23:12.120
Why, you...!

324
00:23:12.120 --> 00:23:15.040
But, once those five minutes are up...

325
00:23:15.710 --> 00:23:20.800
every fiber of your being
will come to know God.

326
00:23:28.800 --> 00:23:30.260
His feet...

327
00:23:32.770 --> 00:23:35.060
I see... a weak spot...

328
00:23:38.730 --> 00:23:40.480
Walk Point!

329
00:23:43.190 --> 00:23:45.200
Can I escape...?

330
00:23:45.200 --> 00:23:47.200
I can't see straight...

331
00:23:48.780 --> 00:23:50.490
You're still moving?

332
00:23:53.580 --> 00:23:55.830
My legs are unsteady...

333
00:23:55.830 --> 00:23:56.960
Also...

334
00:23:57.460 --> 00:24:00.840
the rumble ball is about to wear off...

335
00:24:14.020 --> 00:24:15.640
This is it.

336
00:24:15.640 --> 00:24:17.940
It's time to stop running...

337
00:24:20.270 --> 00:24:21.860
You can beat him!

338
00:24:25.610 --> 00:24:27.320
You little...!

339
00:24:27.320 --> 00:24:29.360
What do you think you're doing?!

340
00:24:30.570 --> 00:24:32.450
Swamp Cloud Burger!

341
00:24:34.450 --> 00:24:38.920
Everyone protects me
because I always run away!

342
00:24:40.880 --> 00:24:43.250
That's why they can't rely on me!

343
00:24:44.500 --> 00:24:48.220
I'm going to raise
a pirate flag right here!

344
00:24:56.890 --> 00:24:59.230
You sore loser.

345
00:24:59.230 --> 00:25:02.810
Even the air is my realm!
Do you still not get it?!

346
00:25:03.270 --> 00:25:04.320
Come!

347
00:25:13.950 --> 00:25:18.290
Aha! He removed my shoe back there!

348
00:25:24.170 --> 00:25:27.300
Damn you and your insolence, tanuki!

349
00:25:33.260 --> 00:25:34.720
I'm a monster!

350
00:25:34.720 --> 00:25:37.970
I'm strong!

351
00:25:37.970 --> 00:25:40.600
The weakest beasts howl the most!

352
00:25:40.600 --> 00:25:43.350
Jet Punch!

353
00:25:51.070 --> 00:25:54.700
I lost my composure
and control of my mantra!

354
00:25:55.620 --> 00:25:57.580
He grazed me! That was close!

355
00:25:58.080 --> 00:25:59.790
Arm Point!

356
00:26:00.460 --> 00:26:01.500
I'm alive!

357
00:26:02.080 --> 00:26:03.080
Cloven...

358
00:26:04.380 --> 00:26:06.090
Cross!

359
00:26:27.690 --> 00:26:32.070
This means I'm a pirate, too!

360
00:26:41.000 --> 00:26:43.620
It looks like he fell right into a swamp!

361
00:26:43.620 --> 00:26:45.000
Thank goodness!

362
00:26:45.000 --> 00:26:46.500
Don't come back up!

363
00:26:46.500 --> 00:26:49.460
Please, just keep on sinking!

364
00:26:52.920 --> 00:26:53.720
He's moving!

365
00:26:57.640 --> 00:26:59.350
He's still alive...!

366
00:26:59.350 --> 00:27:01.600
H-How could I be such a moron...?!

367
00:27:01.600 --> 00:27:04.770
I can't believe a tanuki
got the best of me!

368
00:27:04.770 --> 00:27:07.230
How careless of me!
I'm swamped and sinking!

369
00:27:07.230 --> 00:27:08.860
I must escape!

370
00:27:11.610 --> 00:27:13.780
Don't come back up!

371
00:27:13.780 --> 00:27:15.950
Sink! Sink!

372
00:27:15.950 --> 00:27:17.070
Escape!

373
00:27:17.070 --> 00:27:18.660
Milky Dial!

374
00:27:20.080 --> 00:27:21.870
He really sank!

375
00:27:25.540 --> 00:27:26.270
Y...

376
00:27:27.170 --> 00:27:30.090
Yes! I beat him!

377
00:27:34.260 --> 00:27:36.220
Damn you!

378
00:27:37.970 --> 00:27:40.640
You missed!

379
00:27:42.270 --> 00:27:42.930
Stop!

380
00:27:45.690 --> 00:27:47.940
I said stop!

381
00:27:47.940 --> 00:27:48.690
Nope!

382
00:27:48.690 --> 00:27:50.270
No way!

383
00:27:52.860 --> 00:27:54.740
I said stop it!

384
00:27:55.150 --> 00:27:56.820
They're unconscious!

385
00:27:56.820 --> 00:27:58.360
So what?!

386
00:27:58.360 --> 00:27:59.740
So what?!

387
00:27:59.740 --> 00:28:02.410
These guys killed our brother Satori!

388
00:28:02.410 --> 00:28:03.410
Killed!

389
00:28:03.410 --> 00:28:05.000
– We'll make them pay!
– We'll make them pay!

390
00:28:06.830 --> 00:28:08.290
Why, you...!

391
00:28:09.670 --> 00:28:11.380
Thanks for the impact!

392
00:28:13.670 --> 00:28:14.880
Impact?!

393
00:28:17.180 --> 00:28:19.390
Oh, gross! What is this...?!

394
00:28:22.100 --> 00:28:24.850
I stored farts in a flavor dial!

395
00:28:26.850 --> 00:28:31.650
It appears you have
four types of dials...

396
00:28:33.020 --> 00:28:34.110
That's right!

397
00:28:34.480 --> 00:28:35.360
Axe!

398
00:28:35.360 --> 00:28:36.490
Flame!

399
00:28:36.490 --> 00:28:37.360
Impact!

400
00:28:37.360 --> 00:28:38.490
Flavor!

401
00:28:38.490 --> 00:28:39.820
Got those memorized?!

402
00:28:40.320 --> 00:28:42.200
There's no way to tell us apart!

403
00:28:42.200 --> 00:28:44.830
Which is Hotori, and which is Kotori?!

404
00:28:44.830 --> 00:28:48.250
Which hand has what?
It'll be fun to find out!

405
00:28:48.250 --> 00:28:50.460
– Surprise Dial Illusion!
– Surprise Dial Illusion!

406
00:28:52.040 --> 00:28:55.260
We know what they possess.
There is no time to waste!

407
00:28:55.260 --> 00:28:59.050
I don't give a damn who's who!

408
00:28:59.050 --> 00:29:00.760
Here comes a typhoon!

409
00:29:02.600 --> 00:29:03.970
You missed!

410
00:29:04.390 --> 00:29:06.060
You missed!

411
00:29:06.930 --> 00:29:09.810
Now, what dial is on my right hand?!

412
00:29:14.690 --> 00:29:16.990
Just another fart, you buttheads!

413
00:29:16.990 --> 00:29:18.860
Did you expect flames?!

414
00:29:18.860 --> 00:29:21.070
Those are from my right hand!

415
00:29:21.610 --> 00:29:22.990
He'll ignite the gas!

416
00:29:28.580 --> 00:29:29.500
Weird knight!

417
00:29:31.670 --> 00:29:34.210
We sent that dummy flying!

418
00:29:43.850 --> 00:29:46.970
That sounds like something
a fool would think.

419
00:29:47.430 --> 00:29:50.310
You underestimated me...

420
00:29:50.690 --> 00:29:53.480
Kotori!

421
00:29:55.360 --> 00:29:56.230
Come back!

422
00:29:58.740 --> 00:30:00.190
Cyclone Tempo.

423
00:30:08.370 --> 00:30:10.330
You... Girl...

424
00:30:10.330 --> 00:30:13.710
Finish him off with
my gauntlet down below!

425
00:30:13.710 --> 00:30:15.210
Did your wounds open, weird–

426
00:30:15.210 --> 00:30:17.550
Never mind me! He'll soon return!

427
00:30:18.050 --> 00:30:19.010
Gauntlet?

428
00:30:19.010 --> 00:30:20.880
Gauntlet... Gauntlet...

429
00:30:21.510 --> 00:30:22.760
Gauntlet?!

430
00:30:22.760 --> 00:30:24.640
Hey, what's a gauntlet?!

431
00:30:26.550 --> 00:30:28.220
Whoa, it's heavy!

432
00:30:28.220 --> 00:30:30.430
It is made of Blue Sea iron.

433
00:30:30.850 --> 00:30:33.100
There is an impact dial inside it.

434
00:30:33.100 --> 00:30:34.940
Use it just as I explained.

435
00:30:35.560 --> 00:30:39.900
I think I understand, but I can't
use this thing, it's too heavy...

436
00:30:40.610 --> 00:30:44.160
You'll pay!

437
00:30:44.530 --> 00:30:46.490
Guess there's no time to worry...!

438
00:30:46.490 --> 00:30:50.410
First Big Brother Satori,
then Little Brother Kotori...!

439
00:30:50.410 --> 00:30:52.330
Not even praying will save you now!

440
00:30:52.750 --> 00:30:54.960
He's the flame guy, right?

441
00:30:54.960 --> 00:30:58.630
He's sopping wet,
plus the air is full of moisture!

442
00:30:58.630 --> 00:30:59.800
Cool Ball!

443
00:31:02.670 --> 00:31:05.800
Huh? That's just cold. Is that all?!

444
00:31:05.800 --> 00:31:06.640
Yep, that's all!

445
00:31:06.640 --> 00:31:08.760
You use fire, right?

446
00:31:08.760 --> 00:31:11.020
You're mocking me!

447
00:31:11.020 --> 00:31:14.770
Do you think this will
counter my flame dial?!

448
00:31:14.770 --> 00:31:17.360
I'll burn you to a crisp!

449
00:31:21.360 --> 00:31:24.650
Hot air flowing above
the collected cool air...

450
00:31:24.650 --> 00:31:27.160
causes moisture to condense!

451
00:31:28.280 --> 00:31:30.490
Which creates fog!

452
00:31:30.490 --> 00:31:32.540
Fog Tempo!

453
00:31:34.500 --> 00:31:35.670
What the...?! What the...?!

454
00:31:35.670 --> 00:31:37.960
F-F-Fog!

455
00:31:37.960 --> 00:31:39.460
I can't see a thing!

456
00:31:39.460 --> 00:31:40.420
What is this?!

457
00:31:43.210 --> 00:31:44.300
What... the...?!

458
00:31:44.300 --> 00:31:47.220
You! What are you–

459
00:31:47.220 --> 00:31:48.680
Pardon me a sec!

460
00:31:49.100 --> 00:31:50.050
Impact.

461
00:32:00.360 --> 00:32:02.400
That really hurt!

462
00:32:02.400 --> 00:32:04.570
My arm's coming off!

463
00:32:04.570 --> 00:32:07.860
How could you make me
use this, you weird knight?!

464
00:32:07.860 --> 00:32:10.490
The pain will soon subside.

465
00:32:10.490 --> 00:32:12.870
But you performed wonderfully, lass.

466
00:32:18.080 --> 00:32:18.960
But...

467
00:32:18.960 --> 00:32:22.000
Yes! We protected the ship and crew!
